Christian Bros. Investment Opposes News Corp. Board Re-Election

-- B y   A n t h o n y   P a l a z z o
-- 
2011-09-30T17:32:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/christian-bros-investment-opposes-news-corp-board-re-election.html
Christian Brothers Investment
Services urged investors to oppose the re-election of  News
Corp. (NWSA) ’s board, including Chairman  Rupert Murdoch .  “Through their votes, investors can signal their support
for the appointment of an independent chair,”  Julie Tanner ,
assistant director of socially responsible investing at
Christian Brothers, said today in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Palazzo in Los Angeles at 
 apalazzo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
